<br>
My older brother still has one in storage..... the original Deities &amp; Demigods book... back from the 1980s or something.  It's the one with the gay purple hardcover. It's locked up in some attic along with other collector's items and toys from the 1980s when we were growing up as teenagers. <br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>What two mythos were in it that were promptly removed from it?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> <br>
<br>
I don't know what they removed.  Im not up to date with the 3rd Edition D&amp;D material.  I only gloss thru them briefly whenever I see them in game stores.  I will wager that they removed something that had copyright problems!! <br>
<br>
1) They prolly removed the Cthulhu Mythology chapter  and<br>
<br>
2) They prollly removed the Elric of Melnibone Mythos chapter<br>
<br>
<br>
The ORIGINAL Deities &amp; Demigods had so many mythos chapters.... let's see.... <br>
<br>
Aztec/Maya = Quetzalcoatl and pals <br>
<br>
Norse Mythos = Odin Thor Loki and pals <br>
<br>
Cthulhu Mythos = squid-face and pals<br>
<br>
Melnibonean Mythos chapter = Elric and pals<br>
<br>
Greek Mythos = Zeus Hercules, etc<br>
<br>
Japanese = Hachiman Samurai God of War!!!  etc<br>
<br>
Indian = Vishnu, Garuda, Kali, etc <br>
<br>
Egyptian = Set, Isis, Horus etc<br>
<br>
Gods of the Various Sundry Races =  Garl Glittergold, Gruumsh, Corellon, Lolth, Moradin, Yondalla, Maglubiyet, etc <br>
<br>
Finnish Mythos = this was really interesting to me, the gods from the Finnish Kalevala epic <br>
<br>
The major devils and demons of the Abyss and 9 Hells also had their own chapter IIRC <br>
<br>
Sumerian-Babylonian Mythos = I only remember Marduk, the premier demigod of this pantheon.... oh wait there is that goddess Ishtar too  <br>
<br>
Im sure there was at least 1 or 2 chapters that I missed... <br>
<br>
